dataEntryForms.name: Human Health - Sample Processing - Quarterly
dataEntryForms.htmlCode:
Has your site processed human health samples this quarter?

If so, please complete Section 1.

Has your site processed environmental samples this quarter?

If so, please complete Section 2.

Has your site processed food samples this quarter?

If so, please complete Section 3.

 

1. Human Health - Sample Processing - Quarterly

Please indicate (1) the actual number of samples processed for bacterial culture each quarter (if not processed, please write '0').

Please also indicate (2) the number of samples positive for each pathogen. 

Further information, e.g. reports on different pathogens, can be included in the narrative column
Samples Actual number of samples per quarter (if none write 0) Grantee Comments
Cerebrospinal fluid
1a1 Cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) samples processed for bacterial culture (number)
1a2 number of positive CSF samples
Urine
1b1 Urine samples processed for bacterial culture (number)
1b2 number of positive urine samples
Stool
1c1 Stool samples processed for bacterial culture (number)
1c2 number of positive stool samples
Pus/pus swabs
1d1 Pus/pus swabs samples processed for bacterial culture (number)
1d2 number of positive pus samples
Genitourinary
1e1 Genitourinary samples processed for bacterial culture (number)
1e2 number of positive genitourinary samples
Blood cultures
1f1 Blood culture samples processed for bacterial culture (number)
1f2 number of positive blood culture samples
Other specimen types not listed above (e.g. pleural fluid aspirates, abdominal fluid collection aspirates, sputum, etc)
1g1 Other samples processed for bacterial culture (number)
1g2 number of other culture-positive samples

 

 

2. Environmental - Sample Processing - Quarterly

Please indicate the actual number of sample types processed for bacterial culture each quarter
(if not processed, please write '0')
Sample Type Actual number of samples per quarter (if none write 0) Grantee Comments
2a Farm (litter, manure, or environment)
2b Abattoir/slaughterhouse (litter, manure, or environment)
2c Animal drinking water
2d Sewage/Waste water (please indicate the source of the samples)
2e Surface water (rivers/lake)
2f Tap water (i.e. from mains supply)
2g Commercial bottled water
2h Aquaculture water
2i Other (please specify)

 

 

3. Food Safety - Sample Processing - Quarterly

Please indicate the actual number of sample types processed for bacterial culture each quarter
(if not processed, please write '0')
Sample Type Actual number of samples per quarter (if none write 0) Grantee Comments
3a Chicken meat or chicken products
3b Eggs or egg products
3c Pork or pork products
3d Beef or beef products (cattle, buffalo)
3e Meat or meat products from small ruminants (goats, sheep)
3f Milk or milk products (excludes milk received for mastitis testing)
3g Aquatic animal products (fish, crustaceans, shellfish, frogs)
3h Plant-based foods (e.g. vegetables, fruits)
3i Other (please specify)
